GNOME Activity Journal

Dependencies
------------------------------

You'll need to have Zeitgeist (version 0.3.1 or later) installed.

To get it, run inside the same directory where you have checked out the
"gnome-activity-journal" branch:

 $ bzr get lp:zeitgeist

And then start Zeitgeist in a separate terminal window, running:

 $ ./zeitgeist/zeitgeist-daemon.py

Once Zeitgeist is running, you can start the GNOME Activity Journal like this:

 $ ./gnome-activity-journal/gnome-activity-journal
